Now I have a clear picture. The key finding is:

At line 376-378 in PLXPPollingManager.mm:
```objc
if(self.beforeDisconnectDriverSeatOccupied == XPDriverSeatStateOccupied){
    DLogTagInfo(kBLEKeyPollingTag, @"<PA>主驾有人，不发4G闭锁");
    return;
}
```

This check at 18:00:09 returned `XPDriverSeatStateOccupied`, meaning the system believed the driver seat was occupied, so it didn't send the 4G lock command.


I need to trace back where `beforeDisconnectDriverSeatOccupied` gets set and what the actual `driver_seat_state` value was in the vehicle state logs around the disconnect time to understand why the system thought the seat was occupied.

